    <thetext>Some implementations need much finer-grained support for editing. For example, Google Docs implements a complete text editing framework.

This is extremely difficult in JS currently, yet every modern OS has support for the low-level APIs that make it efficient and practical. These include the ability to find the width of a string, but also the ability to find out where cursor positions would be, etc. Should include support for BIDI positioning also.</thetext>
